.TH HAKMGR "1" "December 2025" "hakmgr 202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hakmgr \- Hacking tools installation and management system
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hakmgr
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,COMMAND\/\fR] [\fI\,PACKAGENAME\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hakmgr
is a specialized package manager for installing, updating, and managing hacking and penetration testing tools. It provides a unified interface for managing security testing tools, ethical hacking utilities, and security research applications from preconfigured GitHub repositories.
.PP
hakmgr supports installation from the hakmgr organization repositories on GitHub, automatic updates via cron scheduling, search functionality for discovering available tools, and proper package version tracking. The tool is designed for security professionals, penetration testers, ethical hackers, and security researchers who need a streamlined way to manage their security toolsets.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B available
List all available hacking tool packages from the GitHub repository
.TP
.B list
List currently installed hacking tool packages
.TP
.B search \fI\,<package>\/\fR
Search for available hacking tool packages matching the specified term
.TP
.B install \fI\,<package>\/\fR
Install a hacking tool package from the preconfigured repository
.TP
.B update \fI\,[package]\/\fR
Update hacking tool packages. If no package is specified, updates all installed packages
.TP
.B download \fI\,<package>\/\fR
Download or clone a hacking tool repository without installing
.TP
.B remove \fI\,<package>\/\fR
Remove an installed hacking tool package and its files
.TP
.B cron \fI\,[package]\/\fR
Manage automatic hacking tool updates via cron job. Can be used to schedule regular updates
.TP
.B version \fI\,<package>\/\fR
Display version information for an installed hacking tool package
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options and installed packages
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output (useful for piping or logging)
.TP
.BR \-\-force
Force installation or operations, bypassing safety checks
.TP
.BR \-\-all
Apply operations to all applicable packages (e.g., update all, remove all)
.TP
.BR \-\-dir " " \fI\,<directory>\/\fR
Set working directory for operations
.SH TOOL CATEGORIES
hakmgr manages various categories of security and hacking tools:
.SS Network Analysis
Tools for network scanning, packet analysis, and network reconnaissance.
.SS Vulnerability Assessment
Vulnerability scanners, exploit frameworks, and security assessment tools.
.SS Password Cracking
Password recovery tools, hash crackers, and authentication testing utilities.
.SS Web Application Security
Web vulnerability scanners, proxy tools, and web application testing frameworks.
.SS Wireless Security
Wi-Fi security testing tools, wireless network analysis utilities.
.SS Exploitation Tools
Exploit frameworks, payload generators, and post-exploitation tools.
.SS Forensics and Analysis
Digital forensics tools, malware analysis utilities, and investigation frameworks.
.SS Social Engineering
Social engineering frameworks and awareness tools.
.SS Reconnaissance
Information gathering tools, OSINT utilities, and reconnaissance frameworks.
.SS Miscellaneous Tools
Additional security utilities, custom scripts, and specialized tools.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B hakmgr list
List all installed hacking tools
.TP
.B hakmgr available
Show all available hacking tools from repository
.TP
.B hakmgr search nmap
Search for nmap and related network scanning packages
.TP
.B hakmgr install metasploit
Install Metasploit penetration testing framework
.TP
.B hakmgr install burpsuite
Install Burp Suite web application security testing tool
.TP
.B hakmgr update
Update all installed hacking tools
.TP
.B hakmgr update metasploit
Update only the Metasploit framework
.TP
.B hakmgr remove aircrack-ng
Remove aircrack-ng wireless security tools
.TP
.B hakmgr download sqlmap
Download sqlmap SQL injection testing tool without installing
.TP
.B hakmgr cron metasploit
Setup or run cron-based updates for Metasploit
.TP
.B hakmgr version nmap
Display version information for installed nmap package
.TP
.B hakmgr \-\-force install john
Force installation of John the Ripper password cracker
.TP
.B hakmgr \-\-all update
Update all installed hacking tool packages
